  "text": "HeLa cells stably expressing BACs with human GFP-tagged APC, Axin-1, DVL2 or CtBP2 were grown at 37°C and 5% CO 2 for at least five passages in SILAC media (Dulbecco's modified eagle medium minus L-arginine and L-lysine (Invitrogen) with 10% dialyzed fetal bovine serum (Invitrogen) and 100 U/mL penicillin/streptomycin (Invitrogen)) containing 49 mg/mL L-arginine (Arg0) and L-lysine (Lys0) (light), 13 C 6 14 N 4 -L-arginine (Arg6) (Euriso-top) and 4,4,5,5-D 4 -L-lysine (Lys4) (medium) or 13 C 6 15 N 4 -L-arginine (Arg10) and 13 C 6 15 N 2 -L-Lysine (Lys8) (heavy) each supplemented with 400 μg/mL Geneticin (Invitrogen). The untransfected control HeLa Kyoto cells were only light or heavy SILAC labeled. Cells were expanded to four, 80% confluent 15 cm dishes per affinity purification and per SILAC label (in total 12 dishes for one triple SILAC experiment). The cell lines were generated by the BAC recombineering technology [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and used as transgenic cell pools.",
